b'' b'... patent law says you can build anything' b'you want to, for your own personal noncommercial use...' b'' b"i'm not up on the details of us patent law, but i think this is incorrect." b'there is a "reasonable use" exemption for *copyright*. there is none for' b'*patents*. the exemptions from patent licensing are quite narrow; r&d work' b"is exempt but personal use is not. that is, it's okay to experiment with" b'a patented idea, but not to put it to practical use (e.g. to improve your' b"stereo), even if it's only your own private practical use." b'' b'of course, it is unlikely that discreet personal use will ever be detected' b'or that you will ever be sued over it.' b'--' 